{"title_page": "Larkin Community Hospital", "text_new": "{{Infobox hospital\n| name        = Larkin Community Hospital\n| org/group   = <!-- Org or group that owns/manages the hospital -->\n| logo        = <!-- Please conform to copyright -->\n| logo_size   = <!-- Use to limit the logo size -->\n| image       = <!-- Preferably photo of the main building or entrance-->\n| image_size  = 225\n| alt         =\n| caption     = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type    =\n| map_alt     = <!-- alternative text for map image, see WP:ALT for details -->\n| relief      = <!-- any non-blank value (yes, 1, etc.) will cause the template to display a relief map image, where available -->\n| coordinates = {{Coord|25.7055856|-80.293116|display=title}}\n| latitude    = <!-- used for adding a map, with map_type, and for displayed coordinates -->\n| longitude   = <!-- used for adding a map, with map_type, and for displayed coordinates -->\n| map_caption = <!-- Optional. Gives a small caption under the map such as \"Shown in region, country\" -->\n| map_size    = <!-- width of the map in pixels (do not include \"px\"); default is 225 -->\n| location    =\n| address     = 7031 Southwest 62nd Avenue\n| region      = [[South Miami]]\n| state       = [[Florida]]\n| country     = [[United States|US]]\n| healthcare  = <!-- UK:NHS. AU/CA: Medicare. ELSE freetext, e.g. Private -->\n| funding     = For-profit<ref name=48acrePurchase />\n| type        = Teaching\n| affiliation = <!-- 'None' or Medical School and university affiliations (medical or paramedical) -->\n| patron      = <!-- 'None' or the individual who acts as the hospital patron -->\n| network     = <!-- Hospital network, non-owner -->\n| standards   = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| emergency   = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/IL/US: I/II/III/IV/V for Trauma certification level -->\n| helipad     = <!-- Yes, No, or use \"Template:Airport codes\" with p=n. Only list if verifiable, leave blank if unknown. -->\n| beds        = 146\n| speciality  = <!-- if devoted to a speciality (i.e. not a broad spectrum of specialities) and Type=Specialist/Teaching -->\n| founded     = <!-- Cite in article as well -->\n| closed      = <!-- Use if defunct, please also add to Category:Defunct hospitals -->\n| website     = {{url|http://larkinhospital.com/site/}}\n| other_links = <!-- Creates \"See also\" field -->\n}}\n'''Larkin Community Hospital''' (LCH) is a [[For-profit hospital|for-profit]] 146-bed general medical, surgical and psychiatric [[teaching hospital]]. In the last year with available data, LCH had about 7,523 [[emergency department]] visits and 5,792 admissions.<ref name=USNews /> [[Physician]]s at the hospital performed 794 inpatient and 739 outpatient surgeries.<ref name=USNews>{{cite web|title=Larkin Community Hospital|url=http://health.usnews.com/best-hospitals/area/fl/larkin-community-hospital-6390993|publisher=US News & World Report}}</ref>\n\nLCH is the only hospital in Miami-Dade County with an Area of Critical Need designation by the Florida Board of Medicine. The hospital is physician-owned, and is accredited by the [[Joint Commission on Accreditation of Healthcare Organizations]] (JCAHO).<ref>{{cite web |title=Larkin Community Hospital Inc: Accreditation History |url=https://www.qualitycheck.org/quality-report/?bsnId=6923|publisher=The Joint Commission}}</ref>\n\n==History== \nIn 2013 LCH was named Top Urban Hospital by The Leapfrog Group.<ref>[http://southfloridahospitalnews.com/page/Larkin_Community_Hospital_Wins_Top_Urban_Hospital_Award/8917/2/?skip=30 \"Larkin Community Hospital Wins Top Urban Hospital Award\"], ''South Florida Hospital News and Healthcare Report'', January 2014</ref>\n\nIn March 2014, LCH began accepting applicants for its new Advance Education in General Dentistry (AEGD) residency program.<ref name=\"Enoughdentists,butwhere?\">{{cite news|last=Dinkova|first=Lidia|title=Enough dentists, but where?|url=http://www.miamitodaynews.com/2014/03/26/enough-dentists/|newspaper=Miami Today|date=March 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2016, Larkin Community Hospital acquired Palm Springs General Hospital now called [[Palm Springs General Hospital|Larkin Community Hospital Palm Springs Campus]], located at 1475 W 49th Pl, Hialeah, FL 33012.<ref>https://www.miamiherald.com/news/health-care/article57963418.html</ref>\n\n==Services==\nThe Miami Neuroscience Center at Larkin offers [[Radiosurgery#Gamma Knife|Gamma Knife\u00ae]] therapy. Gamma Knife is a non-invasive neurological procedure used to treat brain tumors, head and neck cancer, and neurological conditions such as [[trigeminal neuralgia]] and [[arteriovenous malformations]].\n\nThe Dermatology Center at Larkin provides care for dermatological conditions, such as immunobullous disorders, collagen vascular diseases and papulosquamous disorders. The center also treats cutaneous T-cell lymphoma, and chronic graft vs host disease. This center is equipped with photopheresis, hydrotherapy and phototherapy units.\n\nThe Larkin Outpatient Multi Specialty Center offers services in a variety of specialities, including: [[neuromusculoskeletal medicine]], [[sports medicine]], [[orthopedics]], [[cardiology]], [[hematology]], and [[oncology]].\n\n==Graduate medical education==\nLarkin Community Hospital operates a number of [[Residency (medicine)|residency training]] and [[Fellowship (medicine)|fellowship]] programs for newly graduated physicians.  The residencies train physicians specializing in: dermatology, internal medicine, neurology, ophthalmology, physical medicine and rehabilitation, psychiatry, radiology, family medicine, gastroenterology, rheumatology, hematology & oncology, and surgery. All programs are accredited by the [[American Osteopathic Association]], or the [[Accreditation Council for Graduate Medical Education]] (ACGME). LCH also operates [[podiatry]] and [[dentistry]] residency programs. As of 2019, the hospital had 350 medical residents in 30 different programs.<ref name=48acrePurchase>{{cite news|last=Bandell|first=Brian|title=Larkin hospital closes 48-acre purchase for medical school campus|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/southflorida/news/2013/04/23/larkin-hospital-closes-48-acre.html?page=all|newspaper=South Florida Business Journal|date=Apr 23, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe resident physicians at the Larkin Community Hospital obtain training and experience working at affiliated training sites such as:\n* Miami Children's Hospital, Miami, FL\n* Nationwide Children\u2019s Hospital, Columbus, Ohio\n* Borinquen Health Care Center, Miami, FL\n* Miami Beach Community Health Center, Miami, FL\n* Community Health of South Florida (CHI), Miami, FL\n* Jessie Trice Health Community Health Center, Miami, FL\n\n==Campus==\nLarkin Community Hospital is located at 7031 Southwest 62nd Avenue South Miami, Florida 33143.\n\nIn April 2013, LCH purchased a {{convert|43|acre|adj=on}} parcel of land that the hospital intends to use for a new [[Osteopathic medicine in the United States|osteopathic medical]] school campus.<ref name=48acrePurchase /> LCH also plans to move its current nursing school to that new campus, and open future programs in pharmacy and dentistry.<ref name=48acrePurchase />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://larkinhospital.com/site/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Florida]]\n[[Category:Neuroscience research centers in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox hospital\n| name        = Larkin Community Hospital\n| org/group   = <!-- Org or group that owns/manages the hospital -->\n| logo        = <!-- Please conform to copyright -->\n| logo_size   = <!-- Use to limit the logo size -->\n| image       = <!-- Preferably photo of the main building or entrance-->\n| image_size  = 225\n| alt         =\n| caption     = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type    =\n| map_alt     = <!-- alternative text for map image, see WP:ALT for details -->\n| relief      = <!-- any non-blank value (yes